    "faq_gND4cN": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_bDbQJ6": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What electric dirt bikes does Megawheels Dirt Bike offer?",
            "content": "<p>Megawheels D2 Series offers three electric dirt bike models: the D2 Lite,D2 and D2 Pro.<br/>The D2 Lite is an ideal entry-level electric dirt bike, featuring 14\"/12\" wheels, a 3000 W peak mid-drive motor, and a 48V/23.4 Ah battery, delivering a top speed of 38 MPH.<br/>The D2 is the high-performance upgrade, equipped with a 3550W peak mid-drive motor, 48V/26Ah battery, 14\"/12\"wheels, and a top speed of 40 MPH.<br/>The D2 Pro is the flagship model, equipped with a 6000W peak mid-drive motor, 60V/30Ah battery, 17\"/14\" wheels, and a top speed of 50 MPH.<br/>All models come with full hydraulic brakes, dual shock absorption, and three speed modes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_Bgzi89": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the top speed and range of the Megawheels D2 Pro electric dirt bike?",
            "content": "<p>At its top speed of 50mph, the estimated riding time is about 44 minutes, with a range of approximately 18 miles.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "item_kr8eFi": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Why does Megawheels D2 Series Dirt Bike use a mid-drive motor instead of a hub motor?",
            "content": "<p>A mid-drive motor offers several key advantages over a hub motor:<br/>- Better handling with a more balanced center of gravity. <br/>- Stronger low-speed torque for climbing and acceleration. <br/>- Better heat dissipation for consistent performance. <br/>- Easier to push when the battery is out. <br/>- Lighter wheels for improved agility and easier maintenance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_RGpWCw": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Which Megawheels  electric dirt bike is right for me - D2 or D2 Pro?",
            "content": "<p>The D2 is ideal for beginners, while the D2 Pro is recommended for riders with prior electric dirt bike experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_KjiXFw": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long does it take to charge a Megawheels D2 Pro electric dirt bike?",
            "content": "<p>7 hours</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_HWMVGq": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is the Megawheels electric dirt bike street legal?",
            "content": "<p>Subject to local regulations. Riders who meet the applicable legal requirements and documentation can ride on public roads where permitted.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_zDnwDA": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What age is the Megawheeels D2 pro electric dirt bike suitable for?",
            "content": "<p>Suitable for riders aged 13+.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_bhiztG": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What warranty does Megawheels offer on its electric dirt bikes?",
            "content": "<p>Megawheels D2 Series electric dirt bikes supports a 30‑day return and refund policy. For returns due to non‑quality issues, customers are required to pay the round‑trip shipping costs. In addition, it comes with a 1‑year warranty.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_dydeDh": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does Megawheels offer free shipping on electric dirt bikes?",
            "content": "<p>Yes, free shipping is offered on all Megawheels electric dirt bikes.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
